  "prompt": "How do you convert gallons to ounces?",
  "response": "To convert gallons to ounces, you need to know the conversion factor between the two units. There are 128 fluid ounces in one gallon. So, to convert from gallons to ounces, you multiply the number of gallons by 128. \n\nHere's the formula: \n\nOunces = Gallons \u00d7 128\n\nFor example, if you have 2 gallons and want to know how many ounces that is, you would do the following calculation:\n\nOunces = 2 gallons \u00d7 128 = 256 ounces \n\nSo, 2 gallons is equal to 256 fluid ounces.",
